
[1]perfectness

   PER'FECTNESS, n. Completeness; consummate excellence; perfection.

   1. The highest degree of goodness or holiness of which man is capable
   in this life.

   And above all things put on charity, which is the bond of perfectness.
   Col.3.

   2. Accurate skill.
